Lady Caron: You must be Lord Heis, please remember my name,

Noble Heis: Have you ever grown vegetables?
Lady Caron: No... I haven't, but why do you ask?

Noble Heis: It's tough, you know! It's nothing but bugs and

Lady Caron: Then, why not give orders to the servants?

Noble Heis: Hahaha, but that wouldn't be fun, would it?

Noble Heis: I may not know what a righteous life is, but I
believe I understand what a fulfilling life means to me.

Noble Heis: I hope Lady Caron can have that too. Your back
figure felt too lonely.

The nobles of Myukos tried to politically exploit Caron's
beauty. Nobles who dreamed of becoming senators demanded
that Caron be sent out into various social circles to find a
convenient partner.

Instead, Caron's life completely changed, with luxurious
meals, beautiful dresses, and surrounded by so many servants
that their faces couldn't be remembered. She quickly became
the center of the social circle, with everyone drawn to
Caron's beauty.

Among them, only the noble Heis was worried about Caron and
gave her advice. Her mother was worried that her own desires
would be fulfilled. However, Heis genuinely worried about
Caron without any lies or deceit...

From that day on, Heis never left Caron's mind. Men who only
saw her beauty. People who tried to use her. Caron was
reminded of her own loneliness for the first time in a
while.

Caron thought that this person might be able to fill her
loneliness... What Caron sought from Heis was simple but
important. In other words, it was the obvious fact that
people cannot live alone.
